                    <span>I read Rubino's book and it scared me. I pray he wrong, but I had a hard time disputing his argument. Before becoming a writer I'd been a real estate developer in Utah during the 80s boom. When the market turned, it fell into a freefall. Everyone who is thinking about speculating in real estate should be forced to read his book. That is unless they enjoy the pain of loss. </span>
                  
              
